This was caused by a single line of code for a few users in Japan, and is now fixed.\
I'm told by Yusuke Terada that\
\
	Those who need this line are only people who meet all of the following conditions:\
	(a) Those who use Japanese input methods.\
	(b) Those who customize the background/foreground colors of TeXShop's source windows.\
	(c) Those who choose a dark color for the background.\
\
For these people, a hidden preference will turn the line back on:\
\
	defaults write TeXShop ResetSourceTextColorEachTime  YES\
\
